Cybernetics

Norbert Wiener defined cybernetics in 1948 as "the scientific study of control and communication in the animal and the machine.

The difficulty of cyber-analysis starts with the problem of fundamentals.  The cyber-security industry is big and there are many options that promise to solve any and all concerns.  However, the problem of cyber-security does not decrease with time.  It might be argued that the sophistication of malicious actors is increasing faster than cyber-security can.  
